import requests
import json
from datetime import datetime

# Access Token v√† Page ID
ACCESS_TOKEN = "your_page_access_token"
PAGE_ID = "your_page_id"
POST_ID = "your_post_id"  # ID b√†i vi·∫øt

# URL c∆° b·∫£n c·ªßa Graph API
BASE_URL = "https://graph.facebook.com/v12.0"

# L∆∞u tr·ªØ th√¥ng tin v√†o file
def save_to_file(user_id, user_name, reason, violation_count):
    filename = "luutru.json"
    entry = {
        "user_id": user_id,
        "user_name": user_name,
        "reason": reason,
        "violation_count": violation_count,
        "banned_at": datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
        "violation_report_link": f"https://example.com/handle_violation/{user_id}"
    }

    try:
        with open(filename, "r+", encoding="utf-8") as file:
            file_data = json.load(file)
            file_data.append(entry)
            file.seek(0)
            json.dump(file_data, file, indent=4, ensure_ascii=False)
            print(f"ƒê√£ l∆∞u vi ph·∫°m c·ªßa {user_name} v√†o file!")
    except FileNotFoundError:
        with open(filename, "w", encoding="utf-8") as file:
            json.dump([entry], file, indent=4, ensure_ascii=False)
            print(f"ƒê√£ t·∫°o file v√† l∆∞u vi ph·∫°m c·ªßa {user_name}!")

# L·∫•y b√¨nh lu·∫≠n
def get_comments():
    url = f"{BASE_URL}/{POST_ID}/comments"
    params = {
        "access_token": ACCESS_TOKEN,
    }
    response = requests.get(url, params=params)
    return response.json()

# Ki·ªÉm tra vi ph·∫°m
def check_violation(comment):
    keywords = ["spam", "l·ª´a ƒë·∫£o", "hack", "link", "scam"]
    for keyword in keywords:
        if keyword in comment.lower():
            print(f"Vi ph·∫°m ph√°t hi·ªán: {comment}")
            return True
    return False

# L·∫•y d·ªØ li·ªáu vi ph·∫°m ƒë√£ l∆∞u
def get_violation_data():
    try:
        with open("luutru.json", "r", encoding="utf-8") as file:
            return json.load(file)
    except FileNotFoundError:
        return []

# C·∫≠p nh·∫≠t v√† x·ª≠ l√Ω b√¨nh lu·∫≠n
def handle_violation(comment, violation_count):
    comment_id = comment["id"]
    message = comment["message"]
    user_id = comment["from"]["id"]
    user_name = comment["from"]["name"]

    if violation_count == 1:
        # L·∫ßn vi ph·∫°m ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n, ch·ªâ x·ª≠ l√Ω v√† l∆∞u t√†i kho·∫£n
        save_to_file(user_id, user_name, reason="Vi ph·∫°m n·ªôi dung b√¨nh lu·∫≠n", violation_count=violation_count)
        hide_comment(comment_id)
        print(f"Vi ph·∫°m ƒë·∫ßu ti√™n: ƒê√£ x·ª≠ l√Ω b√¨nh lu·∫≠n c·ªßa {user_name}")
    elif violation_count > 1:
        # L·∫ßn vi ph·∫°m th·ª© hai ho·∫∑c nhi·ªÅu h∆°n, t·∫°o b√°o c√°o v√† x·ª≠ l√Ω
        save_to_file(user_id, user_name, reason="Vi ph·∫°m nghi√™m tr·ªçng", violation_count=violation_count)
        delete_comment(comment_id)
        print(f"Vi ph·∫°m th·ª© hai: ƒê√£ x·ª≠ l√Ω v√† x√≥a b√¨nh lu·∫≠n c·ªßa {user_name}")
        print(f"Link x·ª≠ l√Ω vi ph·∫°m: https://example.com/handle_violation/{user_id}")

# ·∫®n b√¨nh lu·∫≠n
def hide_comment(comment_id):
    url = f"{BASE_URL}/{comment_id}"
    params = {
        "is_hidden": True,
        "access_token": ACCESS_TOKEN,
    }
    response = requests.post(url, data=params)
    print(f"·∫®n b√¨nh lu·∫≠n ID: {comment_id}")
    return response.json()

# X√≥a b√¨nh lu·∫≠n
def delete_comment(comment_id):
    url = f"{BASE_URL}/{comment_id}"
    params = {"access_token": ACCESS_TOKEN}
    response = requests.delete(url, params=params)
    print(f"X√≥a b√¨nh lu·∫≠n ID: {comment_id}")
    return response.json()

# Ki·ªÉm tra s·ªë l·∫ßn vi ph·∫°m
def check_user_violation(user_id):
    violation_data = get_violation_data()
    count = sum(1 for entry in violation_data if entry["user_id"] == user_id)
    print(f"T·ªïng s·ªë vi ph·∫°m c·ªßa {user_id}: {count}")
    return count

# Tool t·ª± ƒë·ªông ki·ªÉm tra v√† x·ª≠ l√Ω
def auto_moderate():
    comments = get_comments()
    for comment in comments.get("data", []):
        user_id = comment["from"]["id"]
        violation_count = check_user_violation(user_id)

        if check_violation(comment["message"]):
            handle_violation(comment, violation_count + 1)

# Ch·∫°y tool
if __name__ == "__main__":
    auto_moderate()
